n cloves are intended as herbal medicine it is usually as a commercially made supplement either in a pill or <a class="easyazon-link" data-cart="y" data-cloak="n" data-identifier="B000FT50GA" data-locale="US" data-localize="y" data-popups="y" data-tag="herbal-resource-20" href="http://www.amazon.com/gp/aws/cart/add.html?ASIN.1=B000FT50GA&amp;Quantity.1=1&amp;AWSAccessKeyId=AKIAJHDUSG3BK3WTSDKA&amp;AssociateTag=herbal-resource-20" rel="nofollow" target="_blank">capsule form</a> but can also be found as a tincture and an essential oil.</p><p>The manufacturer&#8217;s instructions regarding dosage should always be followed.</p><figure id="attachment_6526" style="max-width: 678px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://i0.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/clover-syzygium-aromaticum-img-e1473847889146.jpg?ssl=1"><img data-attachment-id="6526" data-permalink="https://www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/cloves-benefits-uses.html/clover-syzygium-aromaticum-img/" data-orig-file="https://i0.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/clover-syzygium-aromaticum-img-e1473847889146.jpg?fit=678%2C400&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="678,400" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="clover-syzygium-aromaticum-img" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i0.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/clover-syzygium-aromaticum-img-e1473847889146.jpg?fit=300%2C177&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i0.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/clover-syzygium-aromaticum-img-e1473847889146.jpg?fit=678%2C400&amp;ssl=1" class="size-full wp-image-6526" src="https://i0.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/clover-syzygium-aromaticum-img-e1473847889146.jpg?resize=678%2C400&#038;ssl=1" alt="Cloves (Syzygium aromaticum)" width="678" height="400" srcset="https://i0.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/clover-syzygium-aromaticum-img-e1473847889146.jpg?w=678&amp;ssl=1 678w, https://i0.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2016/03/clover-syzygium-aromaticum-img-e1473847889146.jpg?resize=300%2C177&amp;ssl=1 300w" sizes="(max-width: 678px) 100vw, 678px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Cloves (Syzygium aromaticum)</figcaption></figure><h3 align="center">Potential Side Effects of Cloves</h3><p>Cloves are not considered harmful or have any serious side effects when used as seasoning. The essential oil is very strong and should be used with caution and never in its undiluted form or internally.</p><p>In any oil blends intended for therapeutic reasons the clove essential oil should not be present in higher concentrations than 1%, or it may cause skin irritation.</p><p>It is probably safest to avoid using the essential oil during pregnancy and lactation, and the oil should never be used on infants.</p><p align="center"><b>Other Resources I like on Cloves</b></p><p style="text-align: center;"><a href="http://simplegoodandtasty.com/2012/04/24/the-spice-odyssey-cloves" target="_blank">The Spice Odyssey: Cloves</a></p><figure id="attachment_5396" style="max-width: 620px" class="wp-caption aligncenter"><a href="https://i2.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/cloves-benefits-uses.jpg?ssl=1"><img data-attachment-id="5396" data-permalink="https://www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/cloves-benefits-uses.html/cloves-benefits-uses-2/" data-orig-file="https://i2.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/cloves-benefits-uses.jpg?fit=620%2C465&amp;ssl=1" data-orig-size="620,465" data-comments-opened="1" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;0&quot;}" data-image-title="cloves-benefits-uses" data-image-description="" data-medium-file="https://i2.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/cloves-benefits-uses.jpg?fit=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1" data-large-file="https://i2.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/cloves-benefits-uses.jpg?fit=620%2C465&amp;ssl=1" class="size-full wp-image-5396" src="https://i2.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/cloves-benefits-uses.jpg?resize=620%2C465&#038;ssl=1" alt="cloves benefits" width="620" height="465" srcset="https://i2.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/cloves-benefits-uses.jpg?w=620&amp;ssl=1 620w, https://i2.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/cloves-benefits-uses.jpg?resize=300%2C225&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i2.wp.com/www.herbal-supplement-resource.com/wp-content/uploads/2015/05/cloves-benefits-uses.jpg?resize=320%2C240&amp;ssl=1 320w" sizes="(max-width: 620px) 100vw, 620px" data-recalc-dims="1" /></a><figcaption class="wp-caption-text">Cloves Benefits and Uses &#8211; ©The Herbal Resource</figcaption></figure><p align="center"><b>Supporting References</b></p><p><span style="font-size: 8pt;">Elkins, Rita: Medicinal Herbs of the Rain Forest. Pleasant Grove, Woodland Publishing 1997.</span><br /> <span style="font-size: 8pt;"> Lawless, Julia: The Illustrated Encyclopedia of Essential Oils. Shaftesbury, 